FBIS3-32670 "drlat030_l_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Bolivia Aranibar Notes Willingness To Approach Mercosur PY1202155394 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 12 Feb 94 PY1202155394 La Paz Radio Fides Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Bolivian Foreign Minister Antonio Aranibar pointed out yesterday in the capital of the Oriental Republic of Uruguay that Bolivia is willing to gradually -- and with increased strength -- approach the member countries of the Common Market of the South, Mercosur, made up of Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, and Uruguay. Aranibar is in Montevideo, the capital of the Oriental Republic of Uruguay, where he is participating in a Latin American Integration Association, Aladi, meeting. There are problems regarding the participation of Mexico -- which has already signed an agreement with Canada and the United States -- as far as the free trade agreement is concerned.
